The paper focuses on studying the relationship between players' personality and game behavior in League of Legends, which is a multiplayer online battle arena (MOBA) game. This involves analyzing data on players' behaviors and personality traits, which suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

Firstly, cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a likely sub-category as the paper explores how personality affects behavior in an online game, which has implications for how people interact with technology and each other. 

Secondly, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another likely sub-category as the paper analyzes data on players' behaviors and personality traits, which can be seen as a social network. 

Thirdly, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible sub-category as the paper explores how personality affects behavior in an online game, which has implications for how people interact with technology. 

Fourthly, cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible sub-category as the paper focuses on analyzing data from a multiplayer online game, which involves strategic decision-making and competition. 

Lastly, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible sub-category as the paper uses linear mixed effects (LME) models to describe relationships between players' personality traits and game behavior, which involves statistical modeling and analysis.
